name: FDataRegistryCachePolicy
doc: Rules to use when deciding how to unload registry items and related assets

bCacheIsAlwaysVolatile: If this is true, the cache is always considered volatile when returning EDataRegistryCacheResult
bUseCurveTableCacheVersion: If this is true, the cache version is synchronized with the global CurveTable cache version
MinNumberKept: Will not release items if fewer then this number loaded, 0 means infinite
MaxNumberKept: Maximum number of items to keep loaded, 0 means infinite
ForceKeepSeconds: Any item accessed within this amount of seconds is never unloaded
ForceReleaseSeconds: Any item not accessed within this amount of seconds is always unloaded
